article.headline: Lafayette 38, Bucknell 21
article.story: LEWISBURG, Pa. -- Marc Quilling's three touchdown passes led Lafayette to a 38-21 win over Bucknell on Saturday. Quilling's passing led a balanced offensive attack for Lafayette (7-2, 3-1 Patriot League) while the Leopard defense forced three turnovers. Quilling opened the scoring with a 23-yarder to Joe Russo midway through the first quarter. He had a 51-yarder to Michael Conte in the third quarter and capped the scoring with a TD strike to Shaun Adair early in the fourth. Russo added a touchdown run and Tyrell Coon rushed for 169 yards and a touchdown as the Leopards dominated Bucknell (4-5, 1-3), outgaining the Bison 474 yards to 222. Shaun Pasternak caught touchdown passes of 8 yards from Andrew Lair and 37 yards from Justin Pulgrano for Bucknell. A.J. Kizekai returned a kickoff 100 yards for a touchdown in the first quarter for the Bison. Davis Rodriguez booted a 20-yard field goal with one second left in the second quarter to give Bucknell at 17-14 lead going into halftime. In the third quarter, Quilling hooked up with Conte for a long touchdown and Bucknell responded with Pasternak's second TD catch of the day to cut Lafayette's lead to 24-21. Lafayette needed just five plays to drive 74 yards on the next possession, capped by Coon's 3-yard TD run. Quilling put the game out of reach in the fourth with his 34-yard TD pass to Adair.
